<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFE6FFD9FF71FA18FDABFA4A" blockId="14.[151,1437,1482,1761]" box="[151,598,1482,1509]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<heading id="3E1D4846FFE6FFD9FF71FA18FDABFA4A" bold="true" box="[151,598,1482,1509]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" reason="4">
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FF71FA18FDABFA4A" authority="(Walker, [1858])" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[151,598,1482,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="memorans">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE6FFD9FF71FA18FDABFA4A" bold="true" box="[151,598,1482,1509]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE6FFD9FF71FA18FE70FA4B" bold="true" box="[151,397,1482,1509]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Eudocima memorans</emphasis>
(Walker, [1858])
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2DF0ACA1FFE6FFD9FF71FA3CFA68F94E" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="description">
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFE6FFD9FF71FA3CFD96F9A7" blockId="14.[151,1437,1482,1761]" box="[151,619,1518,1545]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
(
<figureCitation id="FDD1E3AFFFE6FFD9FF79FA3CFF14F9A7" box="[159,233,1518,1545]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="60.[151,250,1932,1956]" captionText="FIGURE 7. Neotropical Eudocima and Ferenta adults (dorsal aspect)." pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Figs 7</figureCitation>
: I–J, 18: D, 23: J, 30: H, 90: A, D)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFE6FFD9FF71F9C0FA68F94E" blockId="14.[151,1437,1482,1761]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
This species is separated from similar 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FDAAF9C1FD34F982" baseAuthorityName="Schaus" baseAuthorityYear="1911" box="[588,713,1555,1580]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anguina">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE6FFD9FDAAF9C1FD34F982" box="[588,713,1555,1580]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E. anguina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as described above. 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FC50F9C0FB5FF982" authorityName="Phalaena" baseAuthorityName="Cramer" baseAuthorityYear="1777" box="[950,1186,1554,1580]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="collusoria">
Eudocima 
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE6FFD9FBD6F9C0FB5FF982" box="[1072,1186,1554,1580]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">collusoria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares a more similar forewing pattern but lacks the small, elongate dark patch on the distal side of the pm line between veins Cu2 and Cu1. The apical line is strongly concave in both species, but in 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FC84F989FC0EF9DA" authorityName="Phalaena" baseAuthorityName="Cramer" baseAuthorityYear="1777" box="[866,1011,1626,1652]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="collusoria">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE6FFD9FC84F989FC0EF9DA" box="[866,1011,1626,1652]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E. collusoria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is distinct between vein R5 and the apex whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FEB3F9ADFE16F936" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[341,491,1663,1688]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="memorans">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE6FFD9FEB3F9ADFE16F936" box="[341,491,1663,1688]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E. memorans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is barely discernible between vein R5 and its more rounded apex. 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FB11F9ACFF1BF912" authorityName="Phalaena" baseAuthorityName="Cramer" baseAuthorityYear="1777" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="collusoria">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE6FFD9FB11F9ACFF1BF912" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Eudocima collusoria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a distinct hindwing apical patch whereas there is no trace of one in 
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE6FFD9FBEBF971FA60F912" box="[1037,1437,1698,1724]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FBEBF971FB59F912" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[1037,1188,1699,1724]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="memorans">E. memorans</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FB49F970FA60F912" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[1199,1437,1698,1724]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="memorans">Eudocima memorans</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
has been recorded as far south as 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFE6FFD9FDE9F914FD9CF94E" box="[527,609,1734,1760]" name="Bolivia" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
and ranges from 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFE6FFD9FCC3F914FC7FF94E" box="[805,898,1734,1760]" name="Ecuador" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
east to 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFE6FFD9FC3FF914FB83F94E" box="[985,1150,1734,1760]" name="French Guiana" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
and north to 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFE6FFD9FAF2F914FA6CF94E" box="[1300,1425,1734,1760]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
